===Etymology===
From {{Gr.}} '''[[ανθολογία]]''' (''anthologia'') "flower-gathering", from '''[[ανθολογέω]]''' (''anthologeo'') "to gather flowers", from '''[[άνθος]]''' (''anthos'') "flower" + '''[[λέγω]]''' (''[[lego]]'') "to gather, to pick up, to collect".  ''[[Anthologiai]]'' were collections of small Greek poems and epigrams, because in Greek culture the flower symbolize the finer sentiments that only poetry can express.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|pl=anthologies}}

# A [[collection]] of [[literary]] [[work]]s, such as [[poem]]s or [[short stories]].
#(''by extension'') An [[assortment]] of things.

